Custom Addendum – Additional Project Terms

This Addendum applies only to uses not already permitted by the Creative Commons Attribution–NonCommercial 4.0 International License (“CC BY-NC 4.0”).

1. Commercial Use Requires Permission

Any use of this project, its source code, or any derived material for commercial purposes requires prior written permission from the Author.
Commercial purposes include, but are not limited to:

use within a for-profit company or organization

use in a paid product or service

use that directly or indirectly generates revenue

integration into proprietary systems

To request commercial permission, contact the Author through GitHub.

2. Required Credit (Attribution)

When using this project, derivatives, or outputs of its functionality, you must provide clear and visible credit to the Author in:

documentation

user interfaces where appropriate

publications, blog posts, or research using the project

any redistributed source code

Credit must include:

“Project by <your name or GitHub username>”

3. No Relicensing Without Permission

You may not relicense or sublicense this project under any commercial or proprietary license without prior written permission from the Author.

4. No Removal of Attribution Notices

You may not remove, obscure, or alter copyright notices, author credits, or references to this Addendum in any distributed form of the project.

5. Enforcement

Violation of this Addendum may result in:

immediate termination of your rights under CC BY-NC-4.0

withdrawal of permission for all uses

pursuit of additional remedies permitted under applicable law

6. Relationship to the Main License

This Addendum does not modify the terms of CC BY-NC-4.0.
It applies in addition to that license and governs scenarios not already covered by it.
